collections.name: First lovley steps
collections.description:
The bird was created in 2019 as part of the St. Johann in Tirol Christmas market. The term “weird bird” is the focus of attention here, and was available as a refrigerator magnet for both men and women.
The image shows an imaginative, black and white drawn bird creature with a humorous and slightly mischievous expression. The bird has a large, curved beak, half-closed, mischievous eyes and ruffled feathers. Its wings are unusually shaped, with one appearing almost like a broken branch.
He sits on a gnarled branch, his claws gripping the wood. The background is a strong, solid color, which contrasts strongly with the monochrome markings of the bird. The shading and detail work give the image an almost cartoonish, yet artistically crafted aesthetic.

collections.name: Love
collections.description:
Love isn’t always soft—it aches, it lingers, it pulls at the deepest parts of the soul. This piece is a reflection of that kind of love—the kind that stays even when the heart is heavy, when distance and pain stretch between two souls that were never meant to be apart.

The textures bleed together like emotions too deep for words, each stroke a whisper of longing, of devotion, of a love that refuses to fade. The colors crash and embrace, mirroring the turbulence of separation, yet still finding harmony in the chaos.

The love for my partner is flourishing here—in every layer, in every pulse of color, in every moment where love refuses to let go. This is love that aches, love that endures, love that waits.

collections.name: Butterfly woman by Moony
collections.description:
In real Life Moony is a french artist who is painting and drawing real artworks. She dedicates some of her artworks to NFTs. She is known for her "Butterfly woman", honouring the beauty of women.
She paints only what she has seen. The colors on the skin and hair are her interpretation of the light reflections. 
All paintings are made in situ, during sessions with a professional model (woman or man). Painters and sculptors are attending these sessions, which are open only through a professional membership.

collections.name: Cutted Fragments of Perception
collections.description: An abstract exploration of fragmented realities, where sharp edges and layered planes intersect, revealing glimpses of shifting perspectives. The composition reflects the complexity of perception—distorted, reassembled, and ever-changing.

collections.name: Kikfin Passes
collections.description:
KikFin Passes are your gateway to an exclusive world of innovation, adventure, and cutting-edge underwater technology. This collection features two premium membership NFTs:

🔹 Shark Pass – Unlocks VIP perks, early product access, and community benefits.

🔸 Whale Pass – Grants elite privileges, including luxury events, influence over designs, and unique real-world experiences.

Each pass connects you to the future of underwater exploration, blending digital ownership with real-world utility.
